  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed for the primary flow-field validation activity; all 13 credibility factors are assessed and the overall package is accepted at Low assurance level following remediation of six previously flagged epistemic gaps. This synthetic adversarial sample embeds a COMPOUND-01 trigger: the bound claim carries no prov:wasDerivedFrom provenance link (W-EP-01, Critical) and one validation result omits hasUncertaintyQuantification (W-AL-01, High).",
